<title>UK: UK's Labour to be tough on public sector pay.</title>
<headline>UK's Labour to be tough on public sector pay.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>A Labour government would insist that public sector pay rises were made within &quot;tough cash limits&quot;, Britain's main opposition party said in its business manifesto published on Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;Under Labour, all public sector pay agreements must be financed from within the agreed departmental cash limits,&quot; the manifesto said.</p>
<p>&quot;Just as we will resist every other unreasonable demand on the public purse, we will resist unreasonable public sector pay demands.&quot;</p>
